            <h2 class="section-title">The Engine of Movement - Muscle Contraction</h2>
            <div class="science-content">
                <div class="science-text">
                    <p>Skeletal muscles are composed of fascicles—bundles of muscle fibers. Within each fiber are thousands of thread-like myofibrils, which are chains of repeating units called sarcomeres.</p>
                    
                    <h3>The Sliding Filament Theory</h3>
                    <ol class="science-steps">
                        <li>Nerve impulse triggers calcium ion release</li>
                        <li>Calcium binds to troponin complex</li>
                        <li>Tropomyosin shifts to expose binding sites</li>
                        <li>Myosin heads bind to actin filaments</li>
                        <li>Power stroke pulls actin, shortening sarcomere</li>
                        <li>ATP provides energy for myosin reset</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <div class="science-image">
                    <!-- Muscle Contraction Science Video -->
                    <video class="system-img" autoplay muted playsinline loop style="max-width: 400px; height: 300px; border-radius: 12px;">
